The United States strongly condemns the terrorist attack that took place in Grand-Bassam, Côte d'Ivoire. They express their condolences to the families of the victims and offer support to those who were injured. The bravery of the Ivoirian and French security personnel is commended for their response to the situation. The Department of State is working to ensure the safety of American citizens in Côte d'Ivoire. The United States pledges to stand with the Ivoirian people and support the government as it strengthens its institutions. They are also committed to partnering with regional governments and international allies to fight against terrorism in West Africa.